Due to the rising interest in quality assurance programs in medicine, German perinatal data collection has been the focus of many discussions,  and has gone through a thorough change during the last few years. Besides problems of responsibility for data collection and processing, the integration of quality assurance programs for case-related financing, especially the development of a new data set, was a major problem. This article describes the historical evolution, problems of the new data set and its electronic transmission, as well as the new reporting procedure.  
